main event: A witness reported sighting a bright, large object traveling at high speed in Kahoka, Missouri on October 7, 1964.
interesting points: The object was described as being twice as large as a usual aircraft light., The witness stated the object was pulsating and traveling from northeast to southwest., A nearby airport staff confirmed they also saw the object., The witness noted that the object was not a balloon or shooting star., The object suddenly became dark while the sky remained lit.
sighted object: a large, bright, pulsating object in the sky
witness description: The primary witness was driving home when they saw the object, and employees at a nearby airport also reported seeing it.
